    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-predicate">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>àrd</g> can be used (uninflected) as the predicate of the
                verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil am balla <m>àrd</m>? Tha.</gd>
                        <tr>Is the wall high? Yes, it is.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cnoc seo <m>àrd</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>This hill is high.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-mod">
            <h>modifier</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>àrd</g> can be used as a post-modifier of a <a
                    href="?xx=nouns/nouns">noun</a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Càit a bheil an taigh mór? Tha an taigh mór air a’ <m>chnoc
                            àrd</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>Where is the big house? The big house is on the tall hill.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [229]</ref>
                    </li>

                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
